<li><a href="http://aggie-horticulture.tamu.edu/kindergarden/child/com/commun.htm" target="_blank">Considerations to Make Before Starting a Community Garden</a></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Eco-friendly Methods</strong></p>
<p>There are multiple methods of eco-friendly gardening. For example, organic gardening is one of the best ways to create a sustainable food supply and help the environment at the same time. Additionally, hydroponic gardening is also a good way to reduce one's footprint on the environment. Hydroponic growing of vegetables and cooking herbs can be accomplished in very limited space, with a few supplies. One of the easiest ways to create an eco-friendly garden is to also practice composting, which not only cuts down on waste, but also produces wonderful plant fertilizer.</p>
